#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Koko Eating Bananas (Binary Search on Answer)

Is question mein hume minimum eating speed k find karni hai
aisi ki Koko saare bananas h hours ke andar finish kar de.

Brute force mein hum har possible speed check kar sakte hain,
lekin piles[i] bahut bada ho sakta hai, isliye efficient approach chahiye.
Yaha Binary Search on Answer use hota hai.

Key Idea:
Koko ki eating speed k ki range:
minimum = 1
maximum = max(piles)

Agar kisi speed mid par Koko h hours ya usse kam mein saare bananas kha leti hai,
to ho sakta hai aur chhoti speed par bhi answer mil jaaye.
Isliye hum left side search karte hain.

Agar kisi speed mid par Koko ko h se zyada hours lag rahe hain,
to speed kam hai, hume right side jaana padega.

How helper works:
Har pile ke liye required hours = ceil(piles[i] / mid)

Example:
pile = 7, speed = 3
hours = ceil(7/3) = 3

Kyuki:
1st hour -> 3 bananas
2nd hour -> 3 bananas
3rd hour -> 1 banana

Saare piles ke hours add karke totalHours nikalte hain.

Steps:
1. low = 1, high = maximum pile
2. mid = (low + high) / 2
3. mid speed par total required hours nikalo
4. Agar totalHours <= h
   -> speed valid hai
   -> aur minimum chahiye, isliye left side search karo
   -> high = mid - 1
5. Else
   -> speed kam hai
   -> right side jao
   -> low = mid + 1

Loop ke end par low minimum valid speed hoti hai.

Why return low?
Kyuki binary search ke baad low first valid speed par point karta hai
jahan Koko h hours ke andar finish kar sakti hai.

Time Complexity:
maxi() -> O(n)
helper() -> O(n)
Binary Search -> O(log(max pile))
Total -> O(n * log(max pile))

Space Complexity:
O(1)

One line intuition:
Minimum aisi speed find karni hai jisse total eating hours h se zyada na ho,
isliye answer space par binary search lagate hain.

#Code:

class Solution {

    public int maxi(int[] piles){
        int n = piles.length;
        int maxVal = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            maxVal = Math.max(maxVal, piles[i]);
        }
        return maxVal;
    }

    public int helper(int[] piles, int mid){
        int totalHours = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<piles.length; i++){
            totalHours += Math.ceil((double)piles[i] / mid);
        }
        return totalHours;
    }

    public int minEatingSpeed(int[] piles, int h) {
        int low = 1;
        int high = maxi(piles);

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;
            int val = helper(piles, mid);

            if(val <= h){
                high = mid-1;
            }
            else{
                low = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return low;
    }
}
